mixin abstract()
  h2.ui.header
    .content #{en ? 'Abstract' : '概要'}
  .ui.basic.segment
    block abstract
      p This paper presents TextAlive, a graphical tool that allows interactive editing of kinetic typography videos in which lyrics or transcripts are animated in synchrony with the corresponding music or speech.
      p While existing systems have allowed the designer and casual user to create animations, most of them do not take into account synchronization with audio signals. They allow predefined motions to be applied to objects and parameters to be tweaked, but it is usually impossible to extend the predefined set of motion algorithms within these systems.
      p We therefore propose an integrated design environment featuring
      ul
        li GUIs that designers can use to create and edit animations synchronized with audio signals,
        li integrated tools that programmers can use to implement animation algorithms, and
        li a framework for bridging the interfaces for designers and programmers.
      p A preliminary user study with designers, programmers, and casual users demonstrated its capability in authoring various kinetic typography videos.
      .ui.message The system was made publicly available as 
        a(href='https://textalive.jp') TextAlive
        | , a web service for authoring lyric videos, with 
        a(href='https://www.aist.go.jp/aist_e/list/latest_research/2015/20160125/en20160125.html') a press release
        |  on 9/8/2015. Latest information can be found on 
        a(href='https://textalive.jp/events') the TextAlive event page
        |  or 
        a(href='https://scrapbox.io/textalive/TextAlive%E3%81%AE%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BA%E5%B1%A5%E6%AD%B4') its update history
        | .
      .ui.message On 9/18/2020, 
        a(href='https://developer.textalive.jp') TextAlive App <abbr title="Application Programming Interface">API</abbr>
        |  was released for developers. It allows the development of interactive lyric-driven visual media that we name &quot;lyric apps.&quot;
        | For more information, please refer to the follow-up page on 
        a(href=`${basePath}lyric-app-framework`) Lyric App Framework
        | .

mixin presentations()
  h2.ui.header #{en ? 'Presentation materials' : '発表内容'}
  .ui.basic.segment
    .ui.stackable.two.columns.grid
      .column
        h3.ui.header CHI 2015 Fast-forward
        +embed-youtube('//www.youtube.com/embed/lOdt-pf5U8Q')
        .caption: .ui.horizontal.list
          .item
            a(href='//www.youtube.com/watch?v=lOdt-pf5U8Q')
              i.youtube.icon
              | Fast-forward
          .item
            a(href='//www.youtube.com/watch?v=ofczPQZaWMk')
              i.youtube.icon
              | Full version
      .column
        h3.ui.header CHI 2015 #{en ? 'Slides' : '発表スライド'}
        .ui.embed(data-url=publicationsTable[p.publication].entryTags.slides, data-placeholder=`${rootPath}images/background-eee.png`, data-icon='video play outline')
        .caption: .ui.horizontal.list
          .item
            a(href=publicationsTable[p.publication].entryTags.slides)
              i.download.icon
              | #{en ? 'Download' : 'ダウンロード'}
